        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 2:24AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 224 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 3 miles south of Noel to 4 miles north of Elkins.
Movement was northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Dime to Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Hindsville...                     Wesley...
Huntsville...                     Garfield...
Rogers...                         Beaver Lake...
Elkins...                         Kingston...
Forum...                          Larue...
Hiwasse...                        Pea Ridge...
Alabam...                         Cave Springs...
Bentonville...                    Avoca...
Gateway...                        Hobbs State Park...
Centerton...                      Best...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 72 and 93.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for northwestern
Arkansas.</instruction>
